  "merger_description": "Restaurant Brands New Zealand Limited (**Restaurant Brands**) and Yum! Brands, Inc. (**Yum**) propose to acquire, via a joint venture (Taco Ventures Pty Ltd (**JV Co**)):\n\n* 9 Taco Bell restaurants from Restaurant Brands\u2019 subsidiary QSR Pty Ltd, and\n* 20 Taco Bell restaurants from Collins Foods Subsidiary Pty Ltd, a subsidiary of Collins Foods Limited (**Collins**)\n\nRestaurant Brands will control JV Co and hold a 60% interest, while Gardiner Lane Capital, LLC, a wholly owned subsidiary of Yum, will acquire a 40% interest.\n\nYum is a NYSE-listed, US-based restaurant company that owns, operates and franchises various fast-food brands and associated restaurants, including KFC, Pizza Hut and Taco Bell. Yum holds equity in and operates around 70 KFC restaurants in Australia but does not operate or hold equity in any Taco Bell or Pizza Hut restaurants in Australia.\n\nRestaurant Brands is a Yum corporate franchisee. In Australia, it operates 9 Taco Bell restaurants, all of which are in NSW, and 74 KFC restaurants.\n\nCollins is an ASX-listed Australian fast-food corporation that owns and operates 294 KFC restaurants and 20 Taco Bell restaurants in Australia, under franchise arrangements with Yum.",
